A  paper “a simpler method of scoring system in evaluation of Hirsuitism” in AICC RCOG. summary: Dr. Niveditha K J is a Gynecologist and Obstetrician in Vadapalani, Chennai, and has an experience of 6 years in these fields. Dr. Niveditha K J practices at Aakash Fertility Centre & Hospital in Vadapalani, Chennai. She completed her MBBS from Sri Ramachandra Medical College and Research Institute (SRMC) Madras, India in 2013 and MS - Obstetrics & Gynaecology from Sri Ramachandra Medical College and Research in 2017. With a career spanning 10  years, Dr. Niveditha K J has been dedicated to providing comprehensive healthcare services at Aakash Fertility Centre & Hospital in Vadapalani, Chennai. Her role encompasses Cosmetic Gynecology, Obstetrics, Infertility treatment, and Laparoscopic Surgery. Cosmetic Gynecology: Providing aesthetic solutions to enhance the form and function of intimate areas. Specializing in procedures like Vaginoplasty, Labiaplasty, Clitoral Hood Reduction, Monsplasty, Hymenoplasty, Perineoplasty, G-Spot Amplification, and Liposuction, designed to address cosmetic concerns and improve self-confidence. Combining medical expertise with a personalized approach to ensure patient comfort and satisfaction. Obstetrics: Providing comprehensive care and support during pregnancy. Ensuring a safe and healthy childbirth experience. Offering postpartum care to promote the well-being of both mother and baby. Gynecology: Addressing a broad spectrum of women's health concerns and conditions. Specializing in cosmetic gynecology procedures to enhance both form and function. Expertise in managing conditions such as endometriosis, ovarian cyst removal, heavy menstrual bleeding, PCOS etc. Infertility Specialist: Offering specialized treatments and solutions for couples facing fertility challenges. Providing advanced reproductive technologies, includingIn Vitro Fertilization (IVF), Intrauterine Insemination (IUI), Intracytoplasmic Sperm Injection (ICSI), Ovulation Induction, Egg Freezing, Sperm and Egg Donor Programs, Surrogacy, Preimplantation Genetic Testing (PGT), Fertility Preservation. Laparoscopic Surgeon (Obs & Gyn): Performing minimally invasive procedures for gynecological conditions. Expertise in laparoscopic ovarian cyst removal, ensuring a quicker recovery and minimal scarring. Conducting laparoscopic procedures during pregnancy, prioritizing the safety of both mother and child. Prenatal Care: Offering thorough prenatal examinations to monitor the health and well-being of both mother and baby. Providing personalized guidance on nutrition, exercise, and overall well-being during pregnancy. Conducting routine screenings and diagnostic tests to ensure a healthy pregnancy. Childbirth Support: Creating a supportive and empowering birthing experience tailored to the preferences of the mother. Collaborating closely with the expectant mother to develop a personalized birth plan. Utilizing modern techniques to manage pain and discomfort during labor. Postpartum Care: Ensuring a smooth transition to postpartum life with comprehensive care for both mother and baby. Addressing postpartum concerns and offering guidance on breastfeeding and newborn care. Monitoring the physical and emotional well-being of the mother during the postpartum period. Stem Cell Therapies: Pioneering the integration of stem cell therapies in women's health. Utilizing the regenerative potential of stem cells for targeted treatment. Offering innovative solutions for various gynecological and reproductive health conditions.

summary: Dr Abdul Basith completed his MBBS and MD in obstetrics and gynaecology from Annamalai University. He went on to train in minimally invasive gynaecological surgery at the WLH in Gurgaon, Delhi NCR where he obtained his fellowship and diploma in minimal access surgery. He served as faculty at Karpaga Vinayaka Medical College and Research institute, Chengelpet and Sri Ramachandra Medical College and Research Institute, Porur, Chennai. He has served as a visiting consultant at Hiba Hospital, Chennai and Mehta Hospital, Chennai. He visited the National University Hospital in Singapore and trained in Assisted ReproductiveTechniques under the pioneer in the field, Professor P.C. Wong. He further completed his 2 year  post doctoral fellowship in Reproductive Medicine at Apollo Hospital, Greams Road, Chennai under the T.N. MGR Medical university. He is trained in Robotic Surgery by Intuitive Surgicals, USA.  He has many publications to his credit and presented many papers in state and national conferences. He has operated / assisted/ served as organising committee for many national and state live operative workshops. He is a life time Member of the Federation of Obstetric and Gynaecological Societies of India, Indian association of Gynaecological Endoscopists, Indian society of Assisted Reproduction and American Association of Gynaecological Laparoscopy. He is also an associate member of Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists. Presently, he is a consultant Gynae-laparoscopic Surgeon and fertility specialist at Madras Medical Mission, Chennai.
